Package: rcore
Type: Package
Title: Templates and Utilities for nf-core Downstream Analysis and Visualization
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Bhattarai", "Upendra", , "upendrarajbhattarai@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "")),
    person("Pantano", "Lorena", , "lorena.pantano@gmail.com",
           role = "aut",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-3859-3249")))
Description: Provides a collection of R Markdown report templates, ggplot2
    themes, colorblind-friendly colour palettes, and helper functions for
    downstream analysis of nf-core pipeline outputs.  Supported workflows
    include RNA-seq, single-cell RNA-seq, ChIP-seq/ATAC-seq, spatial
    transcriptomics, methylation, and multi-omics.  Templates are
    personalised at deploy-time using a user-level configuration so that
    any analyst or organisation can brand their own reports.  Originally
    developed at the Harvard Chan Bioinformatics Core.
